ular observations by\namateur astronomers remain important. Indeed such a detailed characterization\nof the Blazhko effect could not be obtained from large-scale surveys, as\ncooperative long time-series observations are needed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Oct 2013 20:12:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-10-17"}
